<center>
<p><b><font size=+3>2. Features of Component-Based Software Engineering</font></b></center>

<ul>
<ul>
<ol>
<ul>
<li>
<b><font size=+1>Techinical Features of Component-Based Systems</font></b></li>
</ul>

<p><br><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. Coupling</b> -- inter-relatedness among components
<ol>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Defined as the
extent to which that components is coupled with other components. Low coupling
is desired.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Relationship
among components.
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2. Cohesion</b> -- Strength of association
among elements within a component
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The extent to
which the component contained elements are inter-related. High cohesion
is desired.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Relation inside
the component.
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3. Number and Size of Components</b>
-- number of components in a system.
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Many small components
and a few large components in the component and system design.</ol>
</ol>
</ul>
</ul>

